🔧 Best Practices

✔ Use meaningful variable names
✔ Use proper data types
✔ Avoid unnecessary type conversion
✔ Understand operator precedence

---

⚠️ Common Mistakes

❌ Using `=` instead of `==`
❌ Wrong data type conversion
❌ Dividing integers incorrectly
❌ Confusing `is` and `==`

---

🧠 Interview Answer (Simple)

> Python data types define the kind of data stored in variables, while operators perform operations like arithmetic, comparison, and logical evaluation.

